for the rest of my life.

326
00:27:38,871 --> 00:27:42,600
Would you come on?
We'll figure something out.

327
00:27:42,706 --> 00:27:47,800
By the way, you may be
older than that.

328
00:27:47,911 --> 00:27:49,968
So now what?

329
00:27:50,078 --> 00:27:53,171
- I'll come and see you every day after school.
- How?

330
00:27:53,281 --> 00:27:55,771
I'll tell them I made
the basketball team.

331
00:27:55,882 --> 00:27:58,178
- I won't have nothin' to do.
- You can get a job.

332
00:27:58,284 --> 00:27:59,779
- Can't get a job.
- Why?

333
00:27:59,804 --> 00:28:01,004
Can't be any different than school.

334
00:28:01,085 --> 00:28:03,279
- What are you good at?
- I don't know. Making spitballs?

335
00:28:03,388 --> 00:28:06,150
- How 'bout a delivery man?
- I don't know how to drive.

336
00:28:06,255 --> 00:28:08,279
Yeah, right.

337
00:28:10,090 --> 00:28:13,387
Cardiological technician.
Civil engineer.

338
00:28:13,493 --> 00:28:16,461
- You're not gonna eat your cherry?
- Go ahead.

339
00:28:18,630 --> 00:28:20,858
- Clerical transcriber.
- Billy.

340
00:28:20,965 --> 00:28:23,626
Yeah.

341
00:28:25,834 --> 00:28:29,859
- Gross. God, that's gross!
- Check, please.

342
00:28:29,971 --> 00:28:32,961
- Go to the next column.
- Collection agent. Company clerk.

343
00:28:33,072 --> 00:28:36,699
- Computer operator. Construction engineer.
- Computer operator?

344
00:28:36,808 --> 00:28:39,401
- What?
- Computer operator. Read that one.

345
00:28:39,510 --> 00:28:42,841
- Josh, will you quit with your stupid computers!
- Just read it.

346
00:28:42,946 --> 00:28:46,880
- "MacMillan Toys." Toys!
- Toys!

347
00:28:46,982 --> 00:28:47,743
Whee-whee-whee-whee, Jags.

348
00:28:49,183 --> 00:28:54,550
"Seeking experienced computer operators
for all levels of system management.

349
00:28:54,653 --> 00:28:57,450
"Candidates must perform data updates,
malfunction isolation...

350
00:28:57,555 --> 00:28:59,885
- monitoring of cluster performance."
