01:50:15,656 --> 01:50:17,455
Why are you doing this, Josh?

1443
01:50:18,039 --> 01:50:21,005
- There was this carnival in New Jersey.
- Please.

1444
01:50:21,105 --> 01:50:23,167
I made a wish on a machine
called the Zoltar machine.

1445
01:50:23,192 --> 01:50:24,392
Oh, stop it.

1446
01:50:24,473 --> 01:50:25,962
It was a Zoltar machine.

1447
01:50:25,987 --> 01:50:27,986
It had this bobbing head,
and it looked like a devil.

1448
01:50:28,074 --> 01:50:30,431
If you got a quarter
in the devil's mouth,

1449
01:50:30,456 --> 01:50:31,655
you could make a wish, and I did.

1450
01:50:31,741 --> 01:50:34,866
So I made a wish to be big.
That's what I'm trying to tell you.

1451
01:50:34,975 --> 01:50:37,496
I changed into a grown-up,
when I'm really just a kid.

1452
01:50:37,608 --> 01:50:40,267
Fine, Josh, you're a kid.

1453
01:50:42,376 --> 01:50:46,637
Look, I really don't know what it
is that you're trying to tell me...

1454
01:50:46,743 --> 01:50:50,140
but we have a very big presentation
to give tomorrow...

1455
01:50:50,244 --> 01:50:53,043
so I'm gonna get some sleep.

1456
01:52:21,432 --> 01:52:23,366
Hello?

1457
01:52:23,469 --> 01:52:26,267
Yeah, do you have a Zoltar machine?

1458
01:52:26,374 --> 01:52:29,776
- Nope. Never heard of it.
- Yeah. Yeah, thanks.

1459
01:52:40,932 --> 01:52:43,400
Wait. I need a paper.

1460
01:52:43,502 --> 01:52:45,402
Would you get me some gum?

1461
01:52:55,423 --> 01:52:57,083
Thank you.

1462
01:53:18,696 --> 01:53:22,058
These are the notes,
in case you want 'em.

1463
01:53:22,083 --> 01:53:23,285
Thank you.

1464
01:53:31,351 --> 01:53:34,287
Well, should get the cards set
up before everyone comes in.

1465
01:53:36,025 --> 01:53:37,925
Okay.

1466
01:53:48,246 --> 01:53:50,442
Hello?

1467
01:53:50,550 --> 01:53:52,950
- Yeah, do you have a Zoltar machine?
- Got one right here.

1468
01:53:53,053 --> 01:53:54,953
- You do?
- Yeah.

1469
01:53:55,057 --> 01:53:58,028
Yeah! Yeah, thanks. That's great!

1470
01:53:59,099 --> 01:54:01,090
Yeah!

1471
01:54:06,846 --> 01:54:10,749
MacMillan Toys. I'll transfer.

1472
01:54:31,419 --> 01:54:33,980
Right there.
Sea Point Park, New York.

1473
01:54:39,098 --> 01:54:41,533
Well?

1474
01:54:41,637 --> 01:54:44,402
Yes?

1475
01:54:44,509 --> 01:54:47,000
They're waiting for you, Mr. Baskin.

1476
01:54:54,725 --> 01:54:58,753
- Thanks.
- See you around.

1477
01:55:07,680 --> 01:55:11,811
There's this flat screen on the inside
with, uh, with pictures on it...

1478
01:55:11,921 --> 01:55:15,619
and you read it, and you have to make a choice
of what the character's gonna do.

1479
01:55:15,728 --> 01:55:19,762
If he's gonna fight the dragon,
you push one of the buttons...

1480
01:55:19,787 --> 01:55:20,988
Uh...

1481
01:55:23,708 --> 01:55:27,270
- Paul?
- I don't get it.

1482
01:55:27,380 --> 01:55:29,245
- Well...
- Paul, stop it.

1483
01:55:29,350 --> 01:55:31,318
It's a comic book that...

1484
01:55:31,421 --> 01:55:34,756
See, there's a computer chip inside
which stores the choices.

1485
01:55:34,861 --> 01:55:38,696
So, when you reach the end of the
page, you decide where the story goes.

1486
01:55:38,800 --> 01:55:40,995
- That's the point.
- Terrific, Susan.

1487
01:55:41,104 --> 01:55:44,097
The kid makes his own decision.

1488
01:55:44,210 --> 01:55:46,701
- This is really possible?
- Yeah.

1489
01:55:46,813 --> 01:55:50,182
In fact, it's a very simple program.
Isn't that right?

1490
01:55:52,790 --> 01:55:56,159
So what happens
when you run out of choices?

1491
01:55:56,263 --> 01:55:59,666
That's the great thing.
You can just sell different adventures.

1492
01:55:59,769 --> 01:56:03,364
Just pop in a brand-new disk, and
you get a whole new set of options.

1493
01:56:03,476 --> 01:56:06,041
We could market this
on a comic book rack.

1494
01:56:06,066 --> 01:56:07,267
Mm-hmm.

1495
01:56:07,348 --> 01:56:11,547
- I'll be right back.:
- How much would the unit cost?

1496
01:56:12,925 --> 01:56:16,657
Our initial figure is around seven...

1497
01:56:18,801 --> 01:56:21,202
Around seven dollars...

1498
01:56:21,306 --> 01:56:27,111
with a retail cost of about $18.95.

1499
01:56:28,852 --> 01:56:32,379
You expect a kid to pay
$ 19 for a comic book?

1500
01:56:32,491 --> 01:56:34,823
I think a kid...

1501
01:56:40,572 --> 01:56:42,733
Will you excuse me?

1502
01:56:42,842 --> 01:56:46,711
- What's going on?
- Let 'em be.

1503
01:56:51,156 --> 01:56:53,317
Josh?

1504
01:56:53,426 --> 01:56:56,157
Josh?
Oh.

1505
01:57:09,755 --> 01:57:10,588
More.

1506
01:57:10,613 --> 01:57:12,215
Will you take me to
Sea Point Park, New York?

1507
01:57:12,293 --> 01:57:15,286
- Get in.
- Sea Point Park? Josh!

1508
01:57:15,398 --> 01:57:17,366
- Hey! Not so fast!
- Sorry. Here.

1509
01:57:17,467 --> 01:57:20,028
Josh! Josh!

1510
01:57:21,207 --> 01:57:23,368
See you back home!

1511
01:57:23,478 --> 01:57:26,107
Yeah!

1512
01:57:26,215 --> 01:57:29,145
Excuse me. Do you know him?
You know Josh?

1513
01:57:29,170 --> 01:57:30,372
Yeah. Yeah.

1514
01:57:30,457 --> 01:57:33,757
- Look, you have to tell me where he went.
- Who are you?

1515
01:57:34,930 --> 01:57:37,559
I'm... I'm his girlfriend.

1516
01:57:37,669 --> 01:57:41,731
Ew.

1517
01:57:41,842 --> 01:57:44,501
- Billy Kopecki.
- You have to tell me where he went.

1518
01:57:44,526 --> 01:57:45,915
Where did he go?

1519
01:57:45,916 --> 01:57:48,681
Please tell me.

1520
01:57:48,787 --> 01:57:50,846
Tell me!

1521
01:58:11,359 --> 01:58:14,295
It's tough to find
a cab out here. Thanks.

1522
01:59:47,557 --> 01:59:49,650
Work, damn it!

1523
02:00:02,814 --> 02:00:05,716
I wish I was a kid again.

1524
02:00:22,916 --> 02:00:25,317
- Josh?
- Susan.

1525
02:00:25,420 --> 02:00:29,289
You know, you don't
walk out on somebody.

1526
02:00:29,394 --> 02:00:32,922
You don't just get up and leave
and... and... and walk out like that.

1527
02:00:33,034 --> 02:00:36,971
- You don't do that.
- I know. I know. I'm really sorry.

1528
02:00:37,074 --> 02:00:40,340
I'm really sorry,
but I didn't know what to do.

1529
02:00:40,445 --> 02:00:43,210
I didn't know what to say.

1530
02:01:02,516 --> 02:01:05,213
Oh, God.

1531
02:01:05,322 --> 02:01:08,258
You got your wish.

1532
02:01:08,360 --> 02:01:11,091
- I tried to tell you.
- I didn't listen.

1533
02:01:11,198 --> 02:01:13,328
I guess I didn't hear you,
or... or want to, or...

1534
02:01:13,353 --> 02:01:15,154
I tried to tell you last night.

1535
02:01:15,440 --> 02:01:17,568
How would I have... Even if I
did listen, how would I know?

1536
02:01:17,593 --> 02:01:19,094
I've been thinking about this.

1537
02:01:19,179 --> 02:01:21,204
- Why would I know that?
- I've been trying...

1538
02:01:21,315 --> 02:01:24,217
I've been thinking about it, and there's
a million reasons for me to go home...

1539
02:01:24,320 --> 02:01:27,518
but there's only
one reason for me to stay.

1540
02:01:28,895 --> 02:01:31,625
What... What reason is that?

1541
02:01:33,803 --> 02:01:36,602
Well, you.

1542
02:01:38,811 --> 02:01:40,779
Oh, come on. Come on.

1543
02:01:40,881 --> 02:01:44,010
Come on. Come on.
Come on.

1544
02:01:49,196 --> 02:01:51,961
So, uh, what... what are you, 15, 16?

1545
02:01:54,773 --> 02:01:57,504
I'm... I'm 13.

1546
02:02:00,749 --> 02:02:02,740
Mm-hmm.

1547
02:02:02,852 --> 02:02:05,879
Well, that explains it.

1548
02:02:17,710 --> 02:02:20,236
Maybe you could come with me.

1549
02:02:23,287 --> 02:02:25,619
No.

1550
02:02:25,725 --> 02:02:29,388
- No, I...
- Why not?

1551
02:02:29,498 --> 02:02:32,526
I've... I've been there before.

1552
02:02:34,740 --> 02:02:38,643
It's hard enough the first time.

1553
02:02:40,015 --> 02:02:41,983
You know what I mean?

1554
02:02:43,856 --> 02:02:46,382
You don't know what I mean.

1555
02:02:54,975 --> 02:02:56,943
Come on. I'll drive you home.

1556
02:03:03,054 --> 02:03:06,616
- I'm sorry.
- No, I'll be okay.

1557
02:03:06,728 --> 02:03:08,719
You'll be fine.

1558
02:03:08,831 --> 02:03:11,426
Ten years, who knows?

1559
02:03:13,072 --> 02:03:15,438
Maybe you should hold on to my number.

1560
02:03:34,341 --> 02:03:36,400
So this is where you live.

1561
02:03:38,548 --> 02:03:41,950
- Which one is it?
- The one right there.

1562
02:03:42,055 --> 02:03:44,923
Oh. It's nice.

1563
02:03:49,267 --> 02:03:52,761
I'm gonna miss you.

1564
02:03:52,873 --> 02:03:55,239
I'm gonna miss you too.

1565
02:03:59,451 --> 02:04:03,582
- You won't even remember me.
- Oh, yes, I will.

1566
02:05:00,555 --> 02:05:02,989
Bye.

1567
02:06:07,392 --> 02:06:10,191
Ma?

1568
02:06:10,295 --> 02:06:13,459
- Ma, it's me.
- Josh?

1569
02:06:13,568 --> 02:06:16,436
Josh? Josh!

1570
02:06:16,540 --> 02:06:20,033
Oh, my God!
Oh, thank God you're home!

1571
02:06:20,146 --> 02:06:24,083
Oh, Ma,
I missed you all so much.

1572
02:06:33,101 --> 02:06:36,128
- I'm just not good enough.
- What are you talking about?

1573
02:06:36,240 --> 02:06:39,734
You've been hitting the ball over the
fence almost every time in stickball.

1574
02:06:39,846 --> 02:06:41,871
You just gotta get used
to a fatter bat.

1575
02:06:44,588 --> 02:06:46,715
- You really think I could do it?
- Yeah.

1576
02:06:46,825 --> 02:06:48,816
Come on. We'll hit
some after supper.

1577
02:06:48,929 --> 02:06:50,988
Okay, I'll call for you.

